        "message": "Zoom API Secret detected. API Secrets (also called SDK Secrets or Client Secrets) are confidential credentials used together with API Keys to authenticate Zoom API requests and generate JWT tokens. Exposing API Secrets allows attackers to fully authenticate as your application, gaining complete access to create/modify meetings, manage users and accounts, access recordings, control webinars, and perform any API operation your app can perform. Immediately regenerate your API Secret in the Zoom Marketplace app credentials section, update all applications using the compromised secret, and audit all API activity for unauthorized access.",
