        "type": "regex",
        "pattern": "(api_key|apiKey|API_KEY|client_id|clientId|CLIENT_ID|sdk_key|sdkKey|SDK_KEY)[\"'\\s]*[:=][\"'\\s]*[A-Za-z0-9_-]{20,80}",
        "message": "Zoom API Key assignment detected. Direct assignment of API Keys (SDK Keys/Client IDs) in source code exposes your Zoom application identity. While API Keys are considered public in some OAuth flows, hardcoding them alongside secrets increases security risk and makes credential rotation difficult. When compromised with the API Secret, attackers can fully authenticate as your application to access meetings, user data, and perform API operations. Use environment variables or secure configuration management for both API Keys and Secrets.",
